<HTML><HEAD><TITLE>Sustainable Energy Calendar From ME3's Sustainable Minnesota </TITLE></HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF"><IMG  Align=Top SRC="calendar.GIF"><BR>
<BR>
<HR>

To propose an addition to this list please e-mail the information to <a href=mailto:bailey@ilsr.org>John Bailey</a>, Institute for Local Self-Reliance (Tel:  612-379-3815, Fax:  612-379-3920).<BR>
<BR><HR>

<B><CENTER><FONT SIZE=5>Sustainable Energy: Events, Meetings, and Conferences</FONT></CENTER></B><BR><BR>

<UL>
<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>January 26 - 28, 1997, Chatham, MA</B></FONT><BR>
<B>Local Government and Electric Industry Restructuring</B><BR>  Sponsored by Barnstable County Commissioners as part of a national project funded by the Urban Corsortium<BR>
Contact:  Barnstable County Commissioners, PO Box 427, Barnstable Superior Court House, Barnstable, MA  02630
<P>
<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>February 19, 1997, Many Locations </B></FONT><BR>
<B>National Town Meeting on Environmentally Sustainable Energy Choices</B><BR>  Sponsored by Renew America this
Interactive video teleconference will focus on actions local
communities can take to promote and implement sustainable energy
initiatives.  National panelists include Amory Lovins, S. David
Freeman. <P>
Local Minnesota site: World Trade Center, Second Floor Auditorium,
Downtown St. Paul, 12:15-3:15 p.m.  To register or for more
information, email <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:hamilton@me3.org">J. Drake Hamilton</A> (hamilton@me3.org).
<P>


<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>February 25 - 27, 1997, Arlington, VA</B></FONT><BR>
<B>2nd Industrial Energy Efficiency Symposium and Expo</B><BR>  Sponsored by the Office of Industrial Technologies and the US Department of Energy.<BR>
Contact:  Energentics, Inc.  - 7164 Gateway Dr., Columbia, MD 21046.<BR> Fax (301) 621-3329 or E-Mail <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:oit.expo97@hq.doe.gov">oit.expo97@hq.doe.gov</A>
<P>

<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>April 25 - 30, 1997, Washington, D.C.</B></FONT><BR>
<B>Solar 97</B> - National Solar Energy Conference featuring the  26th Annual ASES Annual Conference and the 22nd National Passive Solar Conference.  Co-Sponsored by the U.S. Department of Energy and the American Solar Energy Society <BR>
Contact:  <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.csn.net/solar/">American Solar Energy Society</A>  Tel: 303-443-3130<P>

<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>March 11-13, 1997, Alexandria, VA</B></FONT><BR>
<B>8th Annual U.S. Hydrogen Meeting:  Hydrogen Partneships for the Future</B> - Sponsored by U.S. Department of Energy and the National Hydrogen Association. <BR>
Contact:  <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.ttcorp.com/nha">National Hydrogen Association</A> or Erin O'Donnell at  Tel: 202-223-5547<P>

<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>March 12-15, 1997, Cromwell, CT</B></FONT><BR>
<B>Building Energy:  Insuring a Sustainable Future</B> - Two conferences, workshops and trade show Sponsored by Northeast Sustainable Energy Association<BR>
Contact: <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:nesea@nesea.org">Northeast Sustainable Energy Association</A> - Tel: 413-774-6051<P>

<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>May 25-28, 1997, New York, New York</B></FONT><BR>
<B>8th International Global Warming Conference and Exposition (GW8)</B> - Sponsored by Global Warming International Center (GWIC) USA; Columbia University<BR>
Contact: <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:syshen@megsinet.net">Prof. Sinyan Shen, Chair, International Program Committee</A> - Tel: 630-910-1551, <A HREF="http://www2.msstate.edu/~krreddy/glowar.html">http://www2.msstate.edu/~krreddy/glowar.html</A><P>

<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>July 8-11, 1997, Saratoga Springs, NY</B></FONT><BR>
<B>1997 ACEEE Summer Study on Energy Efficiency in Industry:  How Industry Will Procure Energy Efficiency Services in the 21st Century</B> - Sponsored by <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://crest.org/aceee/">American Council for an Energy-Efficient Economy</A> (ACEEE)<BR>
Contact: <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:ace3-conf@ccmail.pnl.gov">ACEEE</A> - Tel: 202-429-8873<P>

<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>August 24-29, 1997, Montreal, Queb&eacute;c, Canada</B></FONT><BR>
<B>Third Biomass Conference of the Americas:  Making Business from Biomass in Energy, Environment, Chemicals, Fibers and Materials</B> - Sponsored by USDA, DOE, EPA, Natural Resources Canada, Agriculture Canada, Environment Canada, and more.
Contact: <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:rossj@tcplink.nrel.gov">Joan Ross</A>, Conference Executive Secretary, NREL - Fax: 303-275-2905<P>

<LI><FONT SIZE=4><B>October 4-8, 1998, Madison, WI</B></FONT><BR>
<B>Bioenergy '98 - The Eighth National Bioenergy Conference</B> - 
Contact: <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:wiched@mail.state.wi.us">Don Wichert</A>,Wisconsin Energy Bureau - Tel: 608-266-7312<P>
</UL>
