<HTML><!-- This is the page that is the Useful Tools link from Sustainable Minnesota home page-->
<HEAD>
<TITLE>Links to Useful Tools</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=4>Sustainable Minnesota provides these links to useful tools to enable you to use the Internet productively</FONT> <BR>
<BR>

 <FONT SIZE=3>If you want to suggest an addition to the list send a note to <a href=mailto:jbailey@great-lakes.net>John Bailey</a><BR>
<BR>
<HR>
</FONT>

<UL>
<LI><A HREF="http://www.mnonline.org/">MN Online</A> - Everything here is Minnesotan at heart. Comprehensive guide to Minnesota web resources  <P>

<LI><A HREF="http://www.hotbot.com/">HotBot</A>, is one of the newest search engine to hit the net.  Easy to use and has limiting features to focus down your search request to find what you are looking for.  <P>

<LI><A HREF="http://savvy.cs.colostate.edu:2000/">SavvySearch</A>, an experimental search system designed to query nineteen internet search engines simultaneously.   This is a very nice tool. Give it a try.

<LI><!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://metasearch.com/">Metasearch</A>-Scott Banister's newest project that allows you to type search requests once and have them inserted directly into at least seven search engines located on a single page.  It is terrific! <P>


<LI><!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://altavista.digital.com">Alta Vista</A>-Massive Index and Searching Tool to Find Web Pages and Usenet News Postings<P>

<LI><!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://webcrawler.com/">Webcrawler</A>-Searching Tool to Find Web Pages<P>

<LI><!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.dejanews.com/">DejaNews Research Service</A>-Searching Tool To Find Usenet News Postings<P>
       
<LI><!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.liszt.com/">Search for Electronic Mailing Lists</A><P>
    
<LI><!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.cen.uiuc.edu/cgi-bin/find-news">Search for Usenet Newsgroups</A><P>

<LI><!-- Link Tag -->
