<HEAD><TITLE>May 30, 1996 - New Wind Discussion List</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY> 
<H2>News Item - May 30, 1996</H2><P>
 <H3>New Wind Discussion List</H3><P>
The American Wind Energy Association (AWEA) announces the creation of a new mailing list, awea.wind.home, dedicated to discussion of small-scaleenergy systems that include wind.  Here is the statement of purpose forthe list:<P>

This list is intended as a forum for discussion of residential or other small-scale energy systems that make use of wind energy.  Design, fabrication, selection, and installation of residential wind turbines along with associated equipment such as photovoltaics and batteries are all appropriate topices. <P>

If you would like to subscribe to the list, send me a request at <!-- MailTo Tag --><A HREF="MAILTO:tomgray@econet.org">tomgray@econet.org</A>.<P>

We believe this list will fill a need for a relatively specialized discussion area, and look forward to its use.<P>

Tom Gray<BR>
Director of Communications<BR>
<A HREF="http://www.igc.apc.org/awea/">American Wind Energy Association</A><P>

