<HEAD><TITLE>May 21, 1996 - Energy Efficient Financing</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY> 
<H2> News Item - May 21, 1996</H2>
<h3> Energy Efficient Financing and Home Energy Rating Systems</h3>
<P>
Across the nation, leaders, real estate professionals, builders, consumers, and others involved in the houseing industry are beginning to take advantage of Energy Efficient Financing (EEF) products.  EEF products recognize the monthly operating cost savings of energy efficient homes.  They allow underwriting guidelines to be "stretched" to increase consumer purchasing power.  They also make it possible for energy efficient improvements to be included in the cost of a mortgage.  Although available since the early 1980's, EEF products have been underutilized due to limited awareness and the lack of a uniform standard to determine a home's energy efficiency. <P>
Home Energy Rating Systems (HERS) measure and rate the relative energy efficiency of any house regardless of its age, location, construction type or fuel use.  The HERS rating evaluates the heating and cooling systems, glazing strategies, siting and the performance and tightness of the thermal envelope.  The HERS report also includes estimates of annual energy performance and costs and can provide information on cost effective energy efficiency improvements.  It is obtained by an on-site inspection.<P>
HERS are viewed as the linkage to EEF products in that they can provide the lending community with an objective, uniform standard for determining a home's energy efficiency.  Expnaded use of HERS and EEF products can stimulate the use of energy efficiecy technologies, products and home improvements by making efficiency a more quantifiable, visable and recognizable attribute.<P>
A conference on EEF and HERS was held in Minneapolis, Minnesota on May 22, 1996.  It was sponsored by:<P>
<!-- List Tag --><UL TYPE=circle>
<LI>St. Paul Neighborhood Energy Consortium<P>
<LI>Minnesota Environmental Initiative<P>
<LI>Energy Alley<P>
<LI>The McKnight Foundation<P>
</UL>
<P>
For more information contact:<BR>
Minnesota Environmental Initiative<BR>
2420 Rand Tower<BR>
527 Marquette Ave. S.<BR>
Minneapolis, MN  55402-1324<br>
Phone:  612-334-3388, Fax:  612-334-3093<P>
<P>
