<html><head><title>May 15, 1996 - Public Meeting Notice about University
of Minnesota Steam Plants</title></head>
<body><H2>News Item - May 15, 1996</H2>

<b><H3>Public Meeting Notice about University
of Minnesota Steam Plants</b></H3><p>
<b></b><p>
The Minnesota Pollution Control Agency will hold a public information meeting
provide information about the University of Minnesota and Foster Wheeler Twin
Cities, Inc. proposal for modifications to the University's steam plants.<p>
<p>
<b>June 13, 1996 at 7:00 PM</b><p>
<b>DeLaSalle High School on Nicollet Island, Minneapolis</b><p>
<b></b><p>
The University of Minnesota has three steam plants which serve the needs of
both the St. Paul and Minneapolis campuses.  One serves the needs of the St.
Paul campus and the other two the Minneapolis campus.  Foster Wheeler Twin
Cities operates the plants for the University.  The University and Foster
Wheeler Twin Cities are proposing to construct three new boilers for the
Minneapolis campus and one for the St. Paul campus.  After the new boilers came
on-line, eight existing ones would be shut down permanently.  In addition, the
two coal-only fueled boilers will be modified to burn natural gas and
distillate fuel oil as their primary fuels.  (There is more that one boiler at
each steam plant.)<p>
<p>
An air emission permit is required before construction can commence on this
project.  The purpose of the meeting is to provide information about the
project and the draft air emission permit.  Interested persons will have the
chance to ask questions about the project and draft permit at the meeting and
to provide comments.<p>
<p>
An Environmental Impact Statement (EIS) has been prepared for this proposed
project.  The MN Environmental Quality Board has determined the EIS is
adequate.  The draft air emission permit should be available before the
meeting.  To request a copy contact:<p>
<p>
David L Beil<BR>
Air Quality Division<BR>
Minnesota Pollution Control Agency<br>
520 Lafayette Road North<br>
St. Paul, MN  55155<br>
612-296-7810<br>
<p>
Additional materials are available for inspection from 8 - 4:30 M-F at the
Pollution Control Agency, see the above address.<p>

