<HTML> 
<HEAD><TITLE>04-25-96-Greenpeace Rally at NSP Headquarters April 26th-Remembering Chernobyl---Thinking About Prairie Island</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY> 
<H2>News Item-April 25, 1996</H2>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Greenpeace Rally at NSP Headquarters April 26th-Remembering Chernobyl---Thinking About Prairie Island</H2><P>

		

Friday, April 26, is the tenth anniversary of the Chernobyl nuclear disaster.  At 11:00 am, concerned citizens and shareholders will gather at Northern States Power's (NSP's) corporate headquarters (5th Street and Nicollet, downtown Minneapolis) to remember the millions affected by the disaster and call for the phase out of nuclear power as a dangerous and uneconomical source of electricity.<P>

All interested parties are invited to share personal testimony and to bring donations of over teh counter medications, baby food, vitamins and food supplements as part of a worldwide relief effort for the children of Chernobyl.<P>

For more information contact Greenpeace's Minneapolis office, 612-333-1917.



<HR>
