<HEAD><TITLE>04-24-96-Mideast Oil Forever?-Link to Atlantic Monthly article</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY> 
<H2>News Item-April 24, 1996</H2>
<H2 ALIGN=CENTER>Mideast Oil Forever?-Link to Atlantic Monthly Article</H2><P>

		

Here is a link to the Atlantic Monthly article titled, <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.theatlantic.com/atlantic/issues/current/oil/oil.htm">Mideast Oil Forever?</A> from their April 1996 issue.  The article addresses how congressional budget cutters threaten to end America's leadership in new technologies that could generate hundreds of thousands of high wage jobs, reduce damage to the environment, and limit our costly, and dangerous dependency on oil from the unstable Persian Gulf.  The article was written by the U.S. Department of
Energy's Deputy Assistant Secretary of Energy Efficiency and Renewable Energy, Joseph J. Romm, and Deputy Secretary of Energy, Charles B. Curtis.<P>



