<HEAD>
<TITLE>
October 23, 1995-Ethanol 2000 Proposes Minnesota Ethanol Plant
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-October 23, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>Ethanol 2000 Proposes Minnesota Ethanol Plant</H3>

Ethanol 2000, a limited liability corporation, is proposing to construct a dry mill corn ethanol plant in Bingham Lake, MN.  The plant would have the capacity to process 4.5 million bushels of corn per year producing 11.5 million gallons of fuel grade ethanol.  The facility would include a natural gas fired boiler to provide steam for process and other plant use, an a dryer system for the processing of distillers dried grain with solubles to animal feed. <P>

The MN Pollution Control Agency (PCA) has recieved an environmental assessment worksheet from the company which provides the details of the project.  Interested parties can submit comments on the worksheet by November 22, 1995.

<P>
Contact:  Craig Affeldt, PCA Environmental Planning and Review Office, 612-296-7796




