October 21, 1995- Madison Power Company Unconvinced:   Wisconsin  Energy, Northern States Offer Independent Review  
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-October 21, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3> Madison Power Company Unconvinced:   Wisconsin  Energy, Northern States Offer Independent Review   </H3>                                                        
                   
                                                                      
   Wisconsin  Energy  Corp. and Northern States Power Co. modified their merger 
proposal Wednesday by calling for creation of a post inside the new company to  
ensure that all utilities in the region have equal access to major power lines. <P>
                                                                         
   The companies offered the change and other modifications to try to allay     
concerns by opponents who say that the combination of the two Midwestern        
utilities would put too much control of electricity and the system of           
transmitting it into the hands of one company.       <P>                           
                                                                                
   The key element calls for an "independent transmission tariff administrator" 
who would make sure all utilities had the same access to transmission lines when
they shop for the cheapest bulk power in the upper Midwest and Canada.    <P>      
               
                                                                                
   Officials from Wisconsin  Energy  and NSP filed documents with the Federal   
 Energy  Regulatory Commission calling for the new post after opponents of the  
merger said in August that Primergy would own about 75% of the high-voltage     
transmission capacity into Wisconsin.                                                      
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                 
<P>

<I><FONT SIZE=2>Source:  Milwaukee Journal Sentinel,  October  12, 1995    </FONT></I>


