October 16, 1995-Industrial Cogenerators in Florida May Soon Be Able to Sell Excess Statewide
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-October 16, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>Industrial Cogenerators in Florida May Soon Be Able to Sell Excess Statewide </H3>                                                        
                                                                        
                                                                       
    Two recent developments in Florida could provide opportunities for          
industrial cogenerators to increase power sales.  <P>                               
                                                                                
    In one, industrial cogenerators will be allowed to become part of what is   
currently the ''Florida Broker'' system, which will enable them to sell excess  
generation through the state's hourly, economy power sales system. In another,  
the city of Tallahassee is encouraging small cogenerators to participate in a   
request for proposals for the city's electric department to purchase power on a 
long-term basis.           <P>                                                      
                                                                      
    On Sept. 1, the Tallahassee Electric Dept. issued an RFP seeking 250 MW for 
a minimum of 11 years, according to Gary Brinkworth, supervisor of systems      
planning. The RFP process will be open to any party with FERC 211 certification.
The RFP specifically encourages proposals that use renewable fuels or small     
cogeneration facilities. However, to limit impact on system reliability and     
dispatching, no more than 50 MW of those types of power will be considered. <P>     
                                                                                
    A copy of the RFP can be obtained by writing Kent Rickey, Purchasing        
Division, City of Tallahassee, 301 S. Adams Street, Tallahassee, FL 32301, or by
calling Rickey at (904) 891-8788.    <P>                                            

<I><FONT SIZE=2>Source:  Industrial Energy Bulletin, September 8, 1995</FONT></I>


