<TITLE>
October 13, 1995- Report Urges More Renewable  Energy  Technologies
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-October 13, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3> Report Urges More Renewable  Energy  Technologies   </H3>                                                        
                      
                                                                          
   The Congressional Office of Technology Assessment (OTA) in a recent report   
says that renewable  energy  resources could make a significant contribution to 
U.S.  energy  supplies, but that more federal support will be needed if they are
to be developed and to reach their potential.  <P>                                 
                                                                                
    Even though the U.S. has helped 
grow the technologies over past decades and has conducted more research and     
development than any other country, competitive pressure can come from countries
whose governments support major products or technologies.       <P>                
               
                                                                                
   The FY 1995 Department of  Energy  budget for renewable resource development 
is about $315 million. That level of support may result in some modest growth.   
If it were to be reduced and private industry and local and state 
governments do not pick up the slack, there will be no progress until well into 
the next century.    <P>                                                           
                                                                                
   OTA says that more government spending would be in the       
national interest. Policy development will  
depend on how mature a particularly technology is and other factors such as     
competition and world markets. Biomass is cited as a particularly attractive    
area for development.  <P>                                                         
                                                                               
   Copies of the report, "Renewing Our  Energy  Future," are available from the 
Government Printing Office stock number 0520003-01427-1 for $17 each. Credit    
cards are also accepted and orders may be sent to Superintendent of Documents,  
P.O. Box 371954, Pittsburgh, PA 15250-7974 or by fax at 202/512-22501. It is    
also available through OTA Online.                                                                                       
<P>

<I><FONT SIZE=2>Source:  Global Warming Network Online Today , September 28, 1995     </FONT></I>


</BODY> 
</HTML> 
