<TITLE>
October 10, 1995- Mescalero Project Moving Forward, Preparing RFP For Canister         
Technology 
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-October 10, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3> Mescalero Project Moving Forward, Preparing RFP For Canister         
Technology    </H3>                                                        
                                                                      
                                                               
    Scott Northard, project manager of the Mescalero-utility spent fuel storage 
venture and Northern States Power Co employee, told NRC staff last month the storage facility the group wants to build
on Mescalero Apache land in New Mexico would be limited to canister-based       
systems. The group expects to issue requests for proposals (RFP) on the storage 
technology early this month.  <P>                                                  

 Northard told agency staff that the group is in the early    
stages of preparing a license application for the storage facility that it plans
to submit to NRC in December 1996.     Northard stressed that the         
Mescaleros and the more than 20 participating utilities, 12 of which are equity 
partners in the proposed $ 2.3-billion project, are serious about continuing the
work.                                                                                                                                                                                                                           
<P>

<I><FONT SIZE=2>Source:   Nuclear Fuel, September 11, 1995     </FONT></I>


</BODY> 
