<TITLE>
October 7, 1995- NSP, WEPCO Merger Partners to Avoid NRC Antitrust Review   
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-October 7, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>NSP, WEPCO Merger Partners to Avoid NRC Antitrust Review   </H3>
              
                                                                                                                                                  
    Northern States Power Co. (NSP) and Wisconsin  Energy,  parent of Wisconsin 
Electric Power Co. (WEPCO), likely will be able to consummate their planned     
merger without an antitrust review by the Nuclear Regulatory Commission (NRC).  The merger is being reviewed by the Federal  Energy  Regulatory Commission, the U.S. Securities & Exchange   
Commission and public service commissions in four states.  <P>                                                                                                                     
                                                                                
   One or both of the merger partners will have to undergo the    
financial qualification review procedure to assure that the merged company will have adequate financial         
resources to operate the nuclearplants -- NSP's Monticello and Prairie Island-1 and -2 
and WEPCO's Point Beach-1 and -2.                                                               
<P>

<I><FONT SIZE=2> Source:  Inside N.R.C., September 18, 1995  </FONT></I>


</BODY> 
</HTML> 
