<TITLE>
October 5, 1995- Free CD-ROMs Outline Opportunities for Marketing Efficient          
Technologies  
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-October 5, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3> Free CD-ROMs Outline Opportunities for Marketing Efficient          
Technologies  </H3>
                                                                   
                                                                                                                                                
    The federal government is offering two free CD-ROMs that outline            
opportunities to market efficiency technologies and services in the U.S. and    
overseas. The information will also be available on the World Wide Web.   <P>                                
                                                                                
    ''Bridge to a Sustainable Future'' draws on the resources of 11 federal     
agencies involved in environmental and efficiency technologies, and it includes 
information on foreign aid and export assistance programs. The NSTC estimates a 
$ 300-billion worldwide market market, and notes that the U.S. controls almost  
half of that.  <P>                                                                 
                                                                                                                                                             
    One CD-ROM includes more than 150 text documents, guides to associations and
export opportunities and thirty videos illustrating various technologies and the
material can be searched by keyword. The second CD, ''Industry Leadership for a 
Sustainable Future,'' profiles 400 U.S. companies and provides details on their 
products and services. <P>                                   
                                                                                
More information can be obtained from Rich Cooper at (703)750-3934.   <P>                                                              
                                                                                
The material is also be available on the World Wide Web at <!-- Link Tag -->
<A HREF="http://www.gnet.org/">http://www.gnet.org</A>.                                                        

<P>

<I><FONT SIZE=2> Source:  Electric Utility  Week's Demand-Side Report, September 28, 1995   </FONT></I>


</BODY> 
