<TITLE>
October 2, 1995-Ten Wind Projects Will Receive $1.5 Million in DOE Funding  
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-October 2, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>Ten Wind Projects Will Receive $1.5 Million in DOE Funding  </H3>

         
 
The wind energy projects will receive DOE Funding under a program 
known as the Sustainable Technology Energy Partnerships pilot program.   <P>       
                                                                                                                                                            
    The 10 wind projects include wind resource measurement; the assessment of   
bird populations in potential wind plant areas; wind energy deployment; and     
testing of a new variable speed wind turbine generator. The projects will be    
conducted in Nebraska, Oregon, Minnesota, Iowa, New Mexico, California,                                                                                   
Vermont, Alaska and New York. The states will pay for half of the cost of the   
projects.                                                                                                                         
 <P>


<I><FONT SIZE=2>Source:  Inside Energy/with Federal Lands, September 25, 1995   </FONT></I>


