<TITLE>
September 27, 1995-EQB Seeks Alternative Sites for Nuclear Waste Storage
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-September 27, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>EQB Seeks Alternative Sites for Nuclear Waste Storage</H3>

The Environmental Quality Board is seeking proposals for alternative sites for storage of nuclear waste generated at Northern States Power's (NSP's) Prairie Island plants.  Proposed sites must be located in Goodhue County but not on Prairie Island.
<P>


Written submittals must be recieved by the EQB or the EQB's Citizens Site Advisory Task Force by October 26, 1995.  A proposed site must include the descriptive information required in the EQB's Procedures for Dry Cask Storage Siting.  The Task force is scheduled to determine by November 30, 1995, which additional sites it will recommend to the full EQB. <P>

 

The EQB will decide in January 1996 which sites will continue to be considered along with the two already proposed by NSP.  Final site designation is expected by late 1996

<P>
Contact:  Environmental Quality Board, 612-296-2603




