September 25, 1995-MN's Phoenix Industries Producing New Airfoils for Wind Turbines
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-September 25, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>MN's Phoenix Industries Producing New Airfoils for Wind Turbines</H3>

Phoenix Industries of Crookston, LTD., of Crookston, MN, is producing a new type of replacement blades for wind turbines.  The company worked closely with the National Renewable Energy Laboratory to develop the new technology which is helping to improve the energy production of older wind machines in California.  NREL reports that improvements of 10 - 40 percent have been common.  

The new blade design eliminates some of the problems of soiling caused by insects and pollution that has reduced the performance of some older machines. 

<P>
