<TITLE>
September 22, 1995-EQB Seeks Comments on Draft Site Permit For NSP's Next 100 MW of Wind Power
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-September 22, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>EQB Seeks Comments on Draft Site Permit For NSP's Next 100 MW of Wind Power</H3>


Northern States Power Company (NSP) is proposing to construct a 100 MW  Large Wind Energy Conversion System in Lincoln County north of the city of Lake Benton, MN.  The proposed project would consist of 143 turbines built by Zond Systems Inc.  The 700 kW turbines would be spread out over the 11,200 acre site on Buffalo Ridge.<P>

In September, 1994 NSP applied for a Certificate of Site Compatibility for the project under existing law.  A new law covering wind power projects went into effect on August 1, 1995, that requires NSP to be issued a Site Permit for the project.  In September, 1995, NSP asked the Environmental Quality Board (EQB) to consider the application for Certificate of Site Compatibility be considered as an application for a Site Permit.<P>


In accordance with the new statutes (Minnesota Statutes, 116C.694, the EQB has prepared the Draft Site Permit.  Interested parties are encouraged to submit written or oral comments on the Draft Permit by October 6th, 1995.<P>

A copy of the Draft Site Permit can be requested by contacting Larry Hartman, EQB project leader, 612-296-5089 or 1-800-657-3794.<P>



Written comments should be sent or faxed to the following address:<BR>

Larry Hartman<BR>
300 Centennial Building<BR>
658 Cedar Street<BR>
St. Paul, MN  55155<BR>
Fax:  612-296-3698

