<TITLE>
September 2, 1995-MPCA Approves Ethanol Coop's Environmental Assessment Worksheet
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-September 2, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>MPCA Approves Ethanol Coop's Environmental Assessment Worksheet</H3>
On August 29th, the Minnesota Pollution Control Agency(MPCA) Board voted to approve the Findings of Fact for the Environmental Assessment Worksheet (EAW) for the proposed Central Minnesota Ethanol Cooperative (CMEC) in Little Falls, MN.  This project can now proceed in getting the necessary permits and begin construction.<P>

Once built the plant will join a handful of cooperatively-owned ethanol plants around Minnesota.  Ethanol facilities in Minnesota produce nearly 100 million gallons of ethanol each year.  CMEC will be capable of producing 15 million gallons per year.  Minnesota will require the use of oxygenated gasoline statewide beginning in 1997.  By then it is possible that nearly all of the 200 million gallons of ethanol required to meet statewide demand will be produced within the state.<P>

Contact: Bill Blaine, Board Chair-CMEC, 612-632-1614; Craig Affeldt, MPCA, 612-296-7776

</BODY> 
</HTML> 
