<BODY>
<H2>News Item-August 30, 1995</H2>
<HR> 
<H3>Public Hearings Scheduled for August 31 and September 7 on  NSP's Proposed Spent Nuclear Fuel Alternate Storage Site</H3>
On August 28th,the Minnesota Environmental Quality Board announced that two informational meetings would be held to describe the EQB's siting process, receive public comments on the scope of the Environmental Impact Assessment, and respond to questions raised by the public on Northern States Power Company's Application for a Certificate of Site Compatibility for a Goodhue County Independent Spent Nuclear Fuel Storage Facility.  The two meetings will be informational meetings:  formal hearings will be held in mid-1996.<BR><BR>

