August 29, 1995-DPS Announces Utility Deregulation Conference in St. Paul
</TITLE>
</HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H2>News Item-August 29, 1995</H2>
<HR>
 
<H3>DPS To Hold Conference on Competition in the Electric Industry </H3>
The Minnesota Minnesota Department of Public Service has announced a conference titled, "Competition in the Electric Industry:  Opportunities and Choices". The meeting will be held on  Monday, September 25 from 8:00 am - 12:30 pm at the Earle Brown Center of the University of Minnesota's St. Paul campus.  The DPS hopes that the workshop will provide an open forum that seeks to identify factors important to safeguard the public interest in transitioning to a more competitive industry and to consider options and possible solutions to meet these challenges.
 <BR><BR>The Conference is free but participants must pre-register by September 11, 1995. <BR><BR>
Contact:  Judy Schmidt, DPS, 612-296-6830 (Fax:  612-297-1959)


<CENTER>Meeting Location<BR>
<B>St. Paul, MN:</B>  8:00 am-12:30 pm, Monday September 25, 1995<BR>
University of Minnesota, Earle Brown Continuing Education Center, 1890 Buford Avenue<BR><BR>

