<H1>Wind Energy: Property Taxes-HF 3145,SF 2787</H1> 
<H3>January 15, 1997</H3>
For those of you who are still looking at this page, the 1997 Minnesota legislative session began on January 7.  To keep track of 1997 energy initiatives follow this link to <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.me3.org/leg/legwatch97.html">Sustainable Minnesota's 1997 Legislative Watch</A>. 

<H3>February 20, 1996</H3>
This bill was introduced after the defeat of HF 2699.  It addresses only the issue of property taxes<P>

<H3>SF 2787</H3>
 <!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<!-- Link Tag -->
<LI><A HREF="gopher://gopher.revisor.leg.state.mn.us:70/00/.revisor/senate/publicbills/1995-1996/S2700-2799/S787">Text of the Latest Version of the wind bill SF-2787</A><P>
<!-- Link Tag -->
<LI><LI><A HREF="gopher://gopher.revisor.leg.state.mn.us:70/00/.revisor/senate/bill_tracking/number/1995-1996/SF2700-2799/SF2787">Status of the wind bill SF-2787</A><P>


</UL>
<H3>HF 3145</H3>
<!-- List Tag -->
<UL>
<!-- Link Tag -->
<LI><A HREF="gopher://gopher.revisor.leg.state.mn.us:70/00/.revisor/house/publicbills/1995-1996/H3100-2699/H3199">Text of the Latest Version of the wind bill HF-3145</A><P>



<LI><A HREF="gopher://gopher.revisor.leg.state.mn.us:70/00/.revisor/house/bill_tracking/number/1995-1996/HF3100-3199/HF3145">Status of the wind bill-HF 3145</A></UL> <P>



<H1>
Wind Energy:  Mandate, Property Taxes, Eminent Domain-HF 2699,SF 2619</H1> 
<H3>February 6, 1996</H3>
This bill has several components related to wind energy development in Minnesota.  A hearing was held on February 5th, 1996 and the bill was defeated.  Some of the following provisions may reappear later in the session:<P>

<UL>
<LI>The agricultural utilization research institute (AURI) must provide information to resident individual landowners on how to form cooperatives or other forms of business entities to develop wind energy conversion system projects.<P>
<LI>Allows a utility to pass through to ratepayers any property taxes assessed to wind projects that were installed after June 1, 1991, and before January 1, 1997. <P>
<LI>Clarification that all of NSP's mandated wind power development take place within Minnesota.<P>
<LI>Makes it illegal for a utility to use eminent domain to obtain wind easements.<P>
<LI>Property taxes on wind energy systems are modified as follows:
<UL>
<LI>Small-scale wind systems (less than 2 MW) are exempt from property taxes.
<LI>Medium-scale wind systems (between 2 MW and 10 MW) are assessed as follows:  the foundation and support pad are taxable; (ii) the associated supporting and protective structures are exempt for the first five assessment years after they have been constructed, and thereafter, 30 percent of the market value of the associated supporting and protective structures are taxable; and (iii) the turbines, blades, transformers, and its related equipment, are exempt.
<LI>Large-scale wind systems (greater than10 MW) are subject to property taxes and are assessed as follows:  40 percent of the market value of all property is taxable, including (i) the foundation and support pad; (ii) the associated supporting and protective structures; and (iii) the turbines, blades, transformers, and its related equipment. 
</UL>

</UL>

<H3>SF 2619</H3>
