<HEAD><TITLE>Utility Merger BIll - 1996 HF 2642, SF 2337
</TITLE></HEAD> 
<BODY>
<H1>Utility Merger Bill-HF 2642,2337</H1>
<H3>January 15, 1997</H3>
For those of you who are still looking at this page, the 1997 Minnesota legislative session began on January 7.  To keep track of 1997 energy initiatives follow this link to <!-- Link Tag --><A HREF="http://www.me3.org/leg/legwatch97.html">Sustainable Minnesota's 1997 Legislative Watch</A>. 

<H3>February 6, 1996</H3>

 

A bill has been proposed that sets forth regulations for electric public utility mergers that result in a company providing service to over 150,000 customers.  Specifically, the merging utility must annually provide the Public Utilities Commission with information regarding its electricity generation, transmission and distribution systems throughout its service area.  The bill also mandates commission approval for all mergers or consolidations with other utilities.  The authority to issue maintenance standards will be retained by the Public Utilities Commission.  <P>



<H3>SF 2337</H3>
 <!-- Link Tag -->
