<a name="fn8">[9]</a>	Lawrence, David A. and Jeffrey C. Paulson, "Answer of
Applicants," <u>Docket No. E, G-</u>	<u>002/PA-95-500</u>, In the Matter of
NSP's Petition for Approval to Merge with WEC, March 	1, 1996, p. 1.<p>
<a name="fn9">[10]</a>	NSP has proposed reducing customers' electric rates
1.5%, and freezing electric rates for 	four years as a way to pass the
cost-saving benefits of the merger to the customer.<p>
<a name="fn10">[11]</a>	Data for NSP's coal plants were taken from "Power Plant
and Generating Unit Data 	Reports" furnished to the author by NSP.  The data
are available to the public and are 	reported annually to the Minnesota
Department of Public Service.  Numbers for the 	National Average were based on
rated capacity and net generation data from the 	Department of Energy/Energy
Information Administration's "Inventory of Power Plants 	in the U.S.:
1990-94."  Data were not available for 1988 and 1989.<p>
<a name="fn11">[12]</a>	Howard, James J, "Merger of NSP, Wisconsin Energy would
be good for consumers," 	<u>Star Tribune</u>, Opinion from the CEO of NSP, June
14, 1996.<p>
