<H3 ALIGN=CENTER>Environmental Costs of Electricity- Minnesota Regulatory Proceeding</H3>

ME3 is a part of an environmental coalition (Coalition) which is a formal intervenor in a proceeding that will attempt to quantify the environmental cost of generating electricity.  The Coalition is comprised of seven groups including:  ME3, Institute for Local Self-Reliance, Izaak Walton League of America, American Wind Energy Association, Clean Water Action, American Lung Association, and the Minnesota Center for Environmental Advocacy.  In 1993 the Minnesota legislature ordered the Minnesota Public Utilities Commission (PUC) to quantify the environmental costs of electricity (Docket No. E-999/CI-93-583).   On March 22, 1996, an administrative law judge delivered his findings to the PUC.  The PUC issued its final order including the following externality values on December 16, 1996. <P>


<b>MN PUC's Final Environmental Externality Values-December 1996</B>
<!-- Table Tag --><TABLE CELLSPACING=1 CELLPADDING=1 BORDER=1>
<TR><TD></TD><TD>Urban</TD><TD>Metropolitan Fringe</TD><TD>Rural</TD><TD>Within 200 Miles of Minnesota</TD></TR>

<TR><TD>SO2($/ton)</TD><TD>112 - 189</TD><TD>46 - 110</TD><TD>10 - 25</TD><TD>10 - 25</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>PM10($/ton)</TD><TD>4,462 - 6,423</TD><TD>1,987 - 2,886</TD><TD>562 - 855</TD><TD>562 - 885</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>CO($/ton)</TD><TD>1.06 - 2.27</TD><TD>0.76 - 1.34</TD><TD>0.21 - 0.41</TD><TD>0.21  - 0.41</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>NOX($/ton)</TD><TD>371 - 978</TD><TD>140 - 266</TD><TD>18 - 102</TD><TD>18 - 102</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>Pb($/ton)</TD><TD>3,131 - 3,875</TD><TD>1,652 - 1,995</TD><TD>402 - 448</TD><TD>402 - 448</TD></TR>
<TR><TD>CO2($/ton)</TD><TD>.30 - 3.10</TD><TD>.30 - 3.10</TD><TD>.30 - 3.10</TD><TD>.30 - 3.10</TD></TR>
</TABLE><P>



