by a variety of possible emissions forecasts in 1992 to take into account the
reduction in CFCs (another class of greenhouse gas) due to international
agreements, and varying population and economic growth estimates, among other
things.  A number of scenarios were presented in the 1992 Report.  The median
emissions forecast (i.e., the one relying on median case predictions of
economic and population growth) does not differ significantly from the 1990
business-as-usual projection, either in terms of projected CO2 emissions or
projected levels of warming.  <u>Climate Change 1992, The Supplementary Report
