<BODY BGCOLOR="#FFFFFF">
 
<CENTER><FONT SIZE=5><B>Minnesota Electric Utility Deregulation </B></FONT></CENTER><BR>
<BR>
<!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=2>On May 8th, 1995 the Minnesota Public Utilities Commission (PUC) issued an Order that launched an Investigation into Structural and Regulatory Issues in the Electric Utility Industry (PUC Docket #E-999/CI-95-135).  ME3 submitted initial comments to the PUC along with 30 other interested parties. ME3 subscribes to the principle of "Smart Competition" and has proposed a twelve point checklist in order to ensure fair competition.  In its initial order, the PUC notes that since Minnesota possesses a "healthy electric industry",  this is a good opportunity for regulators, industry representatives, and intervenors to "study possible changes in the industry, to observe other jurisdictions, and to decide what, if any, structural and regulatory changes would benefit Minnesota's electric-utility industry." </FONT><P> <!-- Font Tag --><FONT SIZE=3 COLOR="#FF0000">Note:  The Minnesota PUC is NOT online.  Call 612-296-7124  and urge them to make their material available electronically.</FONT><BR>
<BR>
<HR>

